   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "d264526e-9601-4cc8-a236-071555ded48c",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Association rule learning:\n",
    "it is a rule based machine learning algorithm which is used to find the relationships  between the\n",
    "large amount of the datasets\n",
    "\n",
    "our main goal is to identify the frequent patterns and relationships inside the data"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "82b616e9-d665-455a-b018-a0717d71fdb8",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "An association rule is an implication expression in the form of x--->y\n",
    "here x and y represents different items\n",
    "\n",
    "it depends on the customer behaviour\n",
    "\n",
    "milk--->bread that the customer who buy milk there is also a chance of buying bread\n",
    "\n",
    "to evaluate the customer behaviour to buy the items we have to follow some of the mtrics:\n",
    "\n",
    "support\n",
    "\n",
    "confidence\n",
    "\n",
    "lift\n",
    "\n",
    "if a customer buys bread he/she is likely to buy milk"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "a9bf3ddd-9bf0-430d-b56b-30f0fffcca19",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Types of association rule learning:\n",
    "\n",
    "1.Apriori\n",
    "2.Eclat\n",
    "3.F-p growth"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "fe36cc20-44b9-4668-9a61-172d395d1351",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "1.Apriori:\n",
    "\n",
    "it is one of the most and popular algorithm available in unsupervised learning\n",
    "\n",
    "How it works:\n",
    "\n",
    "it uses frequent itemset generation\n",
    "\n",
    "it completely depends on the apriori property\n",
    "\n",
    "steps:\n",
    "\n",
    "set the minimum support\n",
    "\n",
    "find the frequent itemsets\n",
    "\n",
    "generate the candidate itemsets\n",
    "\n",
    "generate association rules"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "6c840cbc-cab1-4384-a5e6-b37d8af02244",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "2.Eclat:\n",
    "it uses depth first search and also vertical data format\n",
    "\n",
    "we require to build the own code for eclat by using functions and control structures"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "66f7d86e-77f3-4c3e-b0e4-0966c27315dd",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "3.F-p growth:\n",
    "\n",
    "it is one of the improved version of apriori algorithm\n",
    "\n",
    "it uses fp tree(frequent pattern tree)\n",
    "\n",
    "some of the step which follows by f-p growth is:\n",
    "\n",
    "1.builds the frequent pattern tree\n",
    "2.identify the frequent patterns\n",
    "3.generate the rules"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "8219c853-e7c2-4a1a-be8f-4ce380ed7b98",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Evaluation metrics in Association rule learning:\n",
    "\n",
    "1.support:\n",
    "\n",
    "how frequently itemsets appears\n",
    "\n",
    "support(x--->y)transaction containing x and y/total number of transactions\n",
    "\n",
    "if 20 out of 100 transactions contain bread and butter\n",
    "\n",
    "support=20/100=0.2(20%)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "3f26282e-821a-494d-8409-1439b72c6d48",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "2.confidence:\n",
    "probability that y is purchased when x is purchased\n",
    "\n",
    "confidence(x--->y)=support(x,y)/support(x)\n",
    "\n",
    "if 20 transactions have bread and butter and 40 transactions have bread\n",
    "\n",
    "confidence=20/40=0.5(50%)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "3b9085b9-d685-4a47-812d-19d00a3b957c",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "3.lift:\n",
    "it helps to measure strength of rule\n",
    "\n",
    "lift(x--->y)=confidence(x--->y)/support(y)\n",
    "lift>1----->positive association\n",
    "lift=1----->no association\n",
    "lift<1--->negative association"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
